# React Component Standards

Follow these patterns when creating React components in the `app/components/` directory.

## Component Structure

Use functional components with TypeScript. Structure components in this order:

1. Type imports (if needed)
2. Component imports from React or other libraries
3. Local imports (relative imports)
4. Type definitions (if simple, inline)
5. Component function
6. Default export

Reference `@app/components/Navigation.tsx` as a canonical example.

## Exports

- Use **default exports** for components
- Component name should match the file name (PascalCase)
- Example: `Navigation.tsx` exports `Navigation` component

```typescript
// Navigation.tsx
export default function Navigation() {
  // component code
}
```

## Naming Conventions

- Component files: PascalCase (e.g., `Navigation.tsx`, `Header.tsx`)
- Component names: PascalCase, matching file name
- Props interfaces: PascalCase with descriptive name (e.g., `NavigationProps`)

## Props

- Define props using TypeScript types or interfaces
- Use `import type` for type-only imports when appropriate
- Props can be inline for simple cases:

```typescript
export default function Component({ prop1, prop2 }: { prop1: string; prop2: number }) {
  // component code
}
```

- Or separate interface for complex props:

```typescript
type ComponentProps = {
  title: string;
  description?: string;
  items: Array<{ id: string; name: string }>;
};

export default function Component({ title, description, items }: ComponentProps) {
  // component code
}
```

## Component Best Practices

- Keep components focused and single-purpose
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks
- Use composition over inheritance
- Prefer props over context for simple data passing
- Keep component files small and maintainable

## TypeScript

- Always use TypeScript for components (`.tsx` extension)
- Type all props explicitly
- Use React's built-in types when appropriate (e.g., `ReactNode` for children)

Example from `@app/layout.tsx`:
```typescript
import type { ReactNode } from "react";

export default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) {
  // layout code
}
```
